edu.metrostate.ics372.thatgroup.clinicaltrial

Class Trial

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.metrostate.ics372.thatgroup.clinicaltrial.Trial
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Trial
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Trial bean is used to hold information about a clinical trial. The trial contains a list of all the patients that have and that currently are, a part of it. The trial class also supports property change notification.
    Author:
    That Group

      • isPatientInTrial

        public boolean isPatientInTrial(Patient patient)
        Returns true if the patient is considered to be in the trial. Please note that a return value of true does not mean the patient is currently active in the trial, it just means that the patient is considered to be or have been a part of this trial.
        Parameters:
        patient - The patient to check. Cannot be null.
        Returns:
        true if the patient is considered to be in the trial; otherwise false.
